column8: SynergyMed Devices is a medical device company focused on the development of cancer tumor treatment products based on an innovative noninvasive ablation technology. The company is registered in the US, based in Boston (with presence in Jerusalem), and is currently at the clinical stage. SynergyMed platform technology may be used as an alternative to surgery for the treatment of early-stage breast, head and neck, skin, and lung cancers for humans and also for the veterinary market. It may also be used for palliative care to relieve pain. The proven technology can locally ablate and destroy cancer tumors, precisely and effectively, without causing any damage to the surrounding healthy tissues. It is based on using specialized electromagnetic applicators which are placed around the region of interest. FDA approved nanoparticles are injected inside the tumor, which absorb the radiated electromagnetic energy efficiently, destroying the tumor without damaging the healthy tissue. The device is controlled through the company’s own developed algorithms which optimize the ablation process while precisely tracking temperature and measuring the administered treatment dose. The company has performed mice studies with breast cancer cell line, showing exceptional results, where the tumor disappeared within only a few days, leaving no scars or traces of cosmetic damage. It has also performed studies on superficial tumors in dogs with excellent results.  SynergyMed Devices Inc. has an experienced team with backgrounds from leading corporate and academic institutions. The company is currently seeking funding and strategic partnerships.

As for skilled developers, DogQ enables users to build automated test scenarios for UI, e2e, regression, functional, and other types of web testing. DogQ allows teams to focus on more important tasks, rather than spending time on tedious or manual testing processes.

column8: Online platform where journalists can pitch story ideas to editors and editors can find journalists on location where they need them. Concept The Pitch Place is here to make freelance journalism a whole lot easier. Our goal is to enable media professionals around the world with the connections they need to tell the stories that matter. In a world where journalists are often taking physical and/or financial risks to work in the field they love as freelancers, the Pitch Place is working to try and reduce those risks every way we can. We are creating a network of media professionals -- including editors, content producers, writers, photographers, videographers, fixers, translators, and experts -- so that: - when breaking news happens, media outlets can easily locate the best freelance talent they need to cover the story immediately - freelancers can pitch story ideas efficiently, based on their expertise and qualifications - editors only receive alerts to story ideas that match their criteria - community standards on pricing, fairness, and copyright are met and respected - journalists know they are working with professionals with a proven track record in the industry - getting paid for a job well done is standard policy - finding the right journalism job for you is a click away How does it work: In each of the following sections, media professionals can connect with each other, agree on the terms of a job, and, once completed, pay and get paid for a job well done. Pitches The Pitch Place is a like a dating service for journalists and editors: each fill out their profile and when a pitch is posted only those who are a match for each other will get an email alert about the details of the pitch. Meanwhile, the teaser and title of the pitch are posted in the community Pitch feed for all registered members to see. Grants, fellowships, awards, events, and PR announcements are also posted on this feed and members can filter the feed to suite their needs. Jobs Journalism jobs, contract positions, freelance gigs -- anything that requires hiring the skills of a media professional are listed on our community Jobs feed. People Members of the Pitch Place are media professionals in the field; the story-tellers; the photojournalists; the writers of history in the making; those capturing life's events in the moment; and the content producers and editors in charge of the gateways reaching the public eye.

Here at SnoopDrive, we know cars — and we know our customers can’t afford to be without one.   Our team of auto industry professionals is passionate about a problem all car owners share — protecting against unexpected repair costs while keeping stress and expenses in check.   Until now, buying a vehicle service contract — aka extended auto warranty — has been a high-pressure process marked by zero trust and sky-high prices. The experience was clearly broken. Yet despite all that, about 50% of new and used car buyers still opt for a service contract at the time of their purchase. So the value is there.   We knew there had to be a better way.   SnoopDrive is our answer.   ·      Our digital application lets customers purchase anytime, anywhere, from any device. ·      Our online process means no sales pitch, no pressure, no "let's make a deal" pricing, and no phone calls. ·      Our products are the best available, simply presented and clearly explained. ·      And we bring all this to market at rates well below standard retail pricing.   SnoopDrive works hard to bring our customers a clear, simple way to protect their car, their pocketbook, and their peace of mind — offering the best products, digitally presented, and at a radically lower price.
